  "body": "I was using using React togather with a small rich text editor named pen:\nhttps://github.com/sofish/pen\nand here my code:\n\n``` coffee\n\n  getInitialState: ->\n    text:         @props.text\n\n  loadPen: ->\n    pen = new Pen\n      editor: @refs.text.getDOMNode()\n      textarea: '<textarea name=\"content\"></textarea>'\n      list: ['bold']\n      stay: false\n    pen.setContent @props.text\n    @refs.text.getDOMNode().focus()\n    pen.on 'change', (content) =>\n      @onChange content.trim()\n    return pen\n\n  onChange: (content) ->\n    console.log content # yes, I found it to be HTML every time\n    @setState text: content\n    time.delay 100, =>\n      console.log @state.text # <--- somtimes @state.text is escaled,\n      # like a string as `innerHTML` changed to another as `textContent`\n    #  @state.text = content # currently my only fix is to rewrting that property again\n```\n\nI don't know how to debug into React and find out what's really happening, but does React do anything like that, escaping HTML state property internally?\n",
